---
/**
 * rest-api/0001 · Figure 1 — "the six REST constraints around a central node".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0001-what-makes-an-api-restful.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source SVG references arrowhead markers (arw, arwA) that the source page
 * defines ONCE in a body-level <svg><defs> block shared by all three figures.
 * To keep each extracted figure self-contained and rendering byte-for-byte, the
 * markers it uses are embedded here in a local <defs> (ids + fills unchanged so
 * the url(#arw)/url(#arwA) references resolve).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 320"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The six REST constraints arranged around a central REST node: client-server, stateless, cacheable, uniform interface, layered system, and optional code-on-demand"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">REST = THE STYLE YOU GET BY APPLYING SIX CONSTRAINTS</text
            >
            <!-- center node -->
            <circle cx="320" cy="170" r="46" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="2"
            ></circle>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="166"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="17"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">REST</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >architectural style</text
            >
            <!-- spokes -->
            <line x1="320" y1="124" x2="320" y2="92" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="282" y1="146" x2="170" y2="92" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="282" y1="194" x2="170" y2="248" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="320" y1="216" x2="320" y2="262" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="358" y1="194" x2="470" y2="248" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="358" y1="146" x2="470" y2="92" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
            ></line>
            <!-- 1 client-server (top) -->
            <rect x="246" y="58" width="148" height="36" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="320" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700"
                >1 · Client–server</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >UI and data evolve apart</text
            >
            <!-- 2 stateless (top-left) -->
            <rect x="22" y="58" width="148" height="36" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="96"
                y="74"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">2 · Stateless</text
            >
            <text x="96" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#244a2e"
                >no server-side session</text
            >
            <!-- 3 cacheable (bottom-left) -->
            <rect x="22" y="246" width="148" height="36" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="96" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700"
                >3 · Cacheable</text
            >
            <text x="96" y="275" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >responses declare freshness</text
            >
            <!-- 4 uniform interface (bottom) -->
            <rect x="246" y="266" width="148" height="38" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="282"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">4 · Uniform interface</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="295" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >one generic contract</text
            >
            <!-- 5 layered system (bottom-right) -->
            <rect x="470" y="246" width="150" height="36" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text x="545" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700"
                >5 · Layered system</text
            >
            <text x="545" y="275" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >proxies &amp; caches slot in</text
            >
            <!-- 6 code-on-demand (top-right) -->
            <rect
                x="470"
                y="58"
                width="150"
                height="36"
                rx="8"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
            <text
                x="545"
                y="74"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">6 · Code-on-demand</text
            >
            <text x="545" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#7a2218"
                >optional · rarely the point</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        An API is "RESTful" only to the degree it honours these. Each trades some freedom for a
        system-wide property — the <em>why</em> is what separates recall from understanding.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
